results.deck: Blue Sky was an American game developer founded in California in 1988. Blue Sky closed down in 2001. The trademark however did not cease to exist until trademark owner Titus Interactive filed for bankruptcy in 2004.
results.description: Blue Sky were most known for their output of sport games, primarily American Football and Baseball games. They also developed a few games based on popular movie licenses such as Jurassic Park and Arachnophobia.
